Package: osktnorm
Type: Package
Title: Normality Transformation Minimizing Asymmetry and Peakedness
Version: 1.0.1
Date: 2026-02-02
Authors@R: 
    person("Zeynel", "Cebeci", 
           email = "cebeciz@gmail.com", 
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Author: Zeynel Cebeci [aut, cre] 
Maintainer: Zeynel Cebeci <cebeciz@gmail.com>
Description: Implements the Optimized Skewness and Kurtosis Transformation
    (OSKT), a moment-targeting normality transformation designed to
    simultaneously reduce asymmetry and excess peakedness in non-normal
    data. The method is based on the Tukey g-and-h distribution, with
    skewness and kurtosis parameters optimized by minimizing an objective
    function derived from the Andersonâ€“Darling goodness-of-fit statistic
    with Stephen's correction factor. Parameter estimation is performed 
    using the L-BFGS-B algorithm to improve the fit to the standard normal
    distribution. The OSKT approach aims to balance symmetry and tail 
    behavior and can be used as an alternative to power-based transformations
    such as Box-Cox and Yeo-Johnson, as well as moment-matching methods based 
    on the Lambert W x F.
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
